This article is a transcript of remarks made by President Donald Trump at Ford's Theatre in Washington, D.C. during the annual gala. The President thanked the performers and guests in attendance and highlighted the importance of celebrating American history and culture. He also praised the legacy of President Abraham Lincoln and the patriotism of the American people. The President mentioned the upcoming commemoration of the 75th anniversary of D-Day and expressed gratitude for the sacrifices made by American soldiers. He concluded his remarks by emphasizing the duty of every patriot to preserve and pass on the values of liberty and justice.